review_blob: Bottle. An excellent wheat beer, probably the best Weizen Ive had, and Im not a big fan of this style. Really nice.
Bottle. Been such a long since Ive tasted this doppelbock. Full body. Beautiful amber. Very nice.
Bottle. Again, long time since Ive drunk this ale, but I remember pretty much of its strong aroma and good flavour. Very nice beer.
Bottle. Long time since Ive drunk this beer. I strongly remember the fruity aroma. A little watery. Nice, refreshing, far above the average Brazilian beer.
Bottle. Long time since Ive drunk this one. Im not the greatest fan of lagers, but this dunkel is worthy every penny. Very good Brazilian beer (rare).
Bottle. Definitely, the best Brazilian beer Ive ever had. Aroma is very good and intense; creamy body. Rich, strong beer. Great!... E vale cada centavo, sem dvida.

Bottle. Gotta say Im not a big fan of lagers. This is one of the VERY few drinkable large-scale beers available in Brazil. At least its 100% barley malt, unlike other watery commercial beers around here. Just drinkable.
